Bare-bones language, really fast, easy to use, very memory unsafe

Common type sizes:

| Type | Size |
| --- | --- |
| char | 1 byte |
| short | usually 2 bytes |
| int | usually 4 bytes |
| long | 4 bytes on Windows, usually 8 bytes on 64-bit Linux/macOS |
| long long | usually 8 bytes |
| float | usually 4 bytes |
| double | usually 8 bytes |
| long double | varies, often 8, 12, or 16 bytes |
| pointer | 4 bytes on 32-bit systems, 8 bytes on 64-bit systems |
| _Bool | usually 1 byte |

C only guarantees minimum ranges for most integer types, so exact sizes can vary by platform and compiler. Use sizeof(type) to check.
